
<purchabr>SENIOR ENGINEERING</purchabr> MAKES <dlramt>12.5 MLN DLR</dlramt> US PURCHASE
    LONDON, March 2 - {<purchaser>Senior Engineering Group Plc</purchaser>} said it
<status>reached agreement</status> with {<seller>Cronus Industries Inc</seller>} to acquire the
whole share capital of {<acquired>South Western Engineering Co</acquired>} for <dlramt>12.5
mln dlrs</dlramt> cash. This sum is being financed by a term loan.
    <acqabr>South Western</acqabr> is one of the U.S.'s leading manufacturers of
<acqbus>heat transfer equipment</acqbus>, with a turnover of 54.86 mln dlrs and
pre-tax profits of 1.72 mln in 1986.
    Completion of the deal is conditional on approval under
U.S. Hart-Scott-Rodino regulations which is expected within 30
days. Some 350,000 dlrs is payable immediately, 12 mln dlrs
payable on completion with the balance due by June 30, 1987.
 Reuter



 